T1  - Communications to the Editor—A Note on “Decomposition of Project Networks”
AU  - Blanning, Robert W.
AU  - Rao, Ambar G.
Y1  - 1965/09/01
PY  - 1965
DA  - 1965/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.12.1.145
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.12.1.145
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 145
EP  - 148
VL  - 12
IS  - 1
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In their paper Management Science, Vol. 11, No. 3, January 1965, pp. 444?459), S. C. Parikh and W. S. Jewell discuss the decomposition of cost-time project networks into subnetworks to aid in finding a cost function for the entire project. They suggest that each subproject be replaced by a set of fictitious activities (in series or in parallel) and that a subsequent analysis be performed using network flow theory. However, when the network configuration is such that series and parallel subprojects can be successively joined to give one project, a simpler method is available, which we wish to present here.
